with all reuerent behauiour in the action it
ſelfe, to haue a ſincere and vpright hart, as

wel in the feare of God to hallow his name,
as to helpe the trueth in neceſſitie: which is
called ſwearing in trueth. Iere. 4. 2. The
ende is to make knowne a very weightie
